  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\n\n    \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n    \n      \n\n\u003cdiv data-analytics-module=\"{\n    \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Hero Menu\u0026#34;,\n    \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Take a look at our 2025 summer travel trends\u0026#34;\n  }\"\u003e\n      \u003cdiv\u003e\n          \n            \u003cp\u003eMar 27, 2025\u003c/p\u003e\n          \n          \n            \u003cp data-reading-time-render=\"\"\u003e[[read-time]] min read\u003c/p\u003e\n          \n        \u003c/div\u003e\n      \n        \u003cp\u003e\n          From dude ranches to distant shores, here’s what’s trending for summer travel.\n        \u003c/p\u003e\n      \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n    \n\n    \n      \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cfigure\u003e\n      \u003cdiv\u003e\n        \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Collage of people enjoying different travel destinations. In the first image, two people lounge on  a tropical beachfront, in the second image, a father and son enjoy a hike, in the third image, two elders embark on a backcountry road trip.\" data-component=\"uni-progressive-image\" fetchpriority=\"high\" height=\"150px\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends.width-200.format-webp.webp\" width=\"360px\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1023px) 100vw,(min-width: 1024px and max-width: 1259) 80vw, 1046px\" data-srcset=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends.width-800.format-webp.webp 800w, https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends.width-1200.format-webp.webp 1200w, https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends.width-1600.format-webp.webp 1600w, https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends.width-2200.format-webp.webp 2200w\"/\u003e\n        \u003c/p\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n      \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n    \n\n    \n    \u003cdiv data-reading-time=\"true\" data-component=\"uni-article-body\"\u003e\n\n            \n              \n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cuni-article-speakable page-title=\"Take a look at our 2025 summer travel trends\" listen-to-article=\"Listen to article\" data-date-modified=\"2025-03-27T15:36:18.697222+00:00\" data-tracking-ids=\"G-HGNBTNCHCQ,G-6NKTLKV14N\" data-voice-list=\"en.ioh-pngnat:Cyan,en.usb-pngnat:Lime\" data-script-src=\"https://www.gstatic.com/readaloud/player/web/api/js/api.js\"\u003e\u003c/uni-article-speakable\u003e\n\n            \n\n            \n            \n\n\n  \n    \u003cdiv data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Paragraph\u0026#34;,\n           \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Take a look at our 2025 summer travel trends\u0026#34;\n         }\"\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"5mt2k\"\u003eSince many of us are beginning our \u003ca href=\"https://blog.google/products/search/summer-travel-tips-ai-overviews-hotel-price-tracking\"\u003esummer travel prep\u003c/a\u003e, we decided to take a look at Google Flights and Search trends for insights — and inspiration — for these upcoming adventures. Here’s a look at what we found:\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 data-block-key=\"24n3s\"\u003eBeach-bound getaways\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"eci6n\"\u003eThe top-trending destinations on Google Flights for summer 2025 include several popular vacation spots — especially coastal and island locations.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n  \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cuni-image-full-width alignment=\"full\" alt-text=\"Image of a list of the top 10 trending international destinations on Google Flights for Summer 2025. Those destinations in order are Curaçao, Osaka, St. Lucia, Tokyo, Rio de Janeiro, Sydney, Tel Aviv, Johannesburg, Cairo, and Aruba.\" external-image=\"\" or-mp4-video-title=\"\" or-mp4-video-url=\"\" section-header=\"Take a look at our 2025 summer travel trends\" custom-class=\"image-full-width--constrained-width uni-component-spacing\"\u003e\n  \n  \n    \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Image of a list of the top 10 trending international destinations on Google Flights for Summer 2025. Those destinations in order are Curaçao, Osaka, St. Lucia, Tokyo, Rio de Janeiro, Sydney, Tel Aviv, Johannesburg, Cairo, and Aruba.\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends_Inline_-_Int.width-100.format-webp.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" data-loading=\"{\n            \u0026#34;mobile\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends_Inline_-_Int.width-500.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;,\n            \u0026#34;desktop\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends_Inline_-_In.width-1000.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;\n          }\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/uni-image-full-width\u003e\n\n\n  \n\n  \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cuni-image-full-width alignment=\"full\" alt-text=\"Image of a list of the top 10 trending Domestic destinations on Google flight for Summer 2025. Those destinations in order are San Juan, Puerto Rico, Billings, Montana, Nantucket, Massachusetts, St. Louis, Missouri, Providence, Rhode Island, Maui, Hawaii, Omaha, Nebraska, Juneau, Alaska, Bangor, Maine, and Madison, Wisconsin.\" external-image=\"\" or-mp4-video-title=\"\" or-mp4-video-url=\"\" section-header=\"Take a look at our 2025 summer travel trends\" custom-class=\"image-full-width--constrained-width uni-component-spacing\"\u003e\n  \n  \n    \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Image of a list of the top 10 trending Domestic destinations on Google flight for Summer 2025. Those destinations in order are San Juan, Puerto Rico, Billings, Montana, Nantucket, Massachusetts, St. Louis, Missouri, Providence, Rhode Island, Maui, Hawaii, Omaha, Nebraska, Juneau, Alaska, Bangor, Maine, and Madison, Wisconsin.\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends_Inline_-_Dom.width-100.format-webp.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" data-loading=\"{\n            \u0026#34;mobile\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends_Inline_-_Dom.width-500.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;,\n            \u0026#34;desktop\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Summer_Travel_Trends_Inline_-_Do.width-1000.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;\n          }\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/uni-image-full-width\u003e\n\n\n  \n\n  \n    \u003cdiv data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Paragraph\u0026#34;,\n           \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Take a look at our 2025 summer travel trends\u0026#34;\n         }\"\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"5mt2k\"\u003eIslands like Puerto Rico, Curacao and St. Lucia are trending, and outside of the Caribbean, people are seeking the sun and the sea in places like Rio de Janeiro, Maui and Nantucket.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"elil4\"\u003eGiven this coastal curiosity, it’s no surprise that “island vacation outfits” are\u003ci\u003e also\u003c/i\u003e currently trending on Search — as are “wide leg linen pants.” (And if you want more inspiration for what to wear, check out \u003ca href=\"https://blog.google/products/shopping/google-shopping-spring-2025-trends/\"\u003eour latest fashion trends\u003c/a\u003e.)\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 data-block-key=\"2nakq\"\u003eOutdoor adventures\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"185t7\"\u003eDestinations with easy access to the great outdoors, like Billings, Montana, Juneau, Alaska and Bangor, Maine are trending in the U.S. And along those same lines, “cabins” are the top-trending type of lodging for romantic getaways, and “dude ranch” is the top-trending type of vacation for families in the U.S. this year.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"dosdp\"\u003eFor shorter weekend getaways, outdoor destinations like upstate New York, Joshua Tree National Park and Sedona, Arizona are also trending on Search.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 data-block-key=\"3r7nl\"\u003eSuper-sized suitcases\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp data-block-key=\"6mkc3\"\u003eFinally, there\u0026#39;s one longer term trend we noticed this year: It looks like people are trying to \u003ci\u003epack\u003c/i\u003e a bit more into every trip — literally. Historically, searches for “carry on bags” surpassed “checked bags.” But in recent years, “checked bags” have been searched more than ever. In fact, \u0026#34;vacuum bags” and “compression packing cubes” are top-trending searches for “best ____ for travel”!\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n  \n    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cuni-image-full-width alignment=\"full\" alt-text=\"Chart showing Google Trends interest over time for the search terms carry on bags (blue line) and checked bags (red line) in the United States from January 1, 2004, to March 25, 2025. The vertical axis represents relative search interest, scaled from 0 to 100. The horizontal axis represents time, with labels for January 1, 2004, and June 1, 2016. There are also vertical lines labeled Note at various points along the timeline. Below the time series, there is a bar chart showing the average interest for both terms over the entire period, with carry on bags having a slightly higher average interest than checked bags. The source is indicated as United States. 1/1/04 - 3/25/25. Web Search.\" external-image=\"\" or-mp4-video-title=\"\" or-mp4-video-url=\"\" section-header=\"Take a look at our 2025 summer travel trends\" custom-class=\"image-full-width--constrained-width uni-component-spacing\"\u003e\n  \n  \n    \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Chart showing Google Trends interest over time for the search terms carry on bags (blue line) and checked bags (red line) in the United States from January 1, 2004, to March 25, 2025. The vertical axis represents relative search interest, scaled from 0 to 100. The horizontal axis represents time, with labels for January 1, 2004, and June 1, 2016. There are also vertical lines labeled Note at various points along the timeline. Below the time series, there is a bar chart showing the average interest for both terms over the entire period, with carry on bags having a slightly higher average interest than checked bags. The source is indicated as United States. 1/1/04 - 3/25/25. Web Search.\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Screenshot_2025-03-27_8.33.19_AM.width-100.format-webp.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" data-loading=\"{\n            \u0026#34;mobile\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Screenshot_2025-03-27_8.33.19_AM.width-500.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;,\n            \u0026#34;desktop\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/Screenshot_2025-03-27_8.33.19_AM.width-1000.format-webp.webp\u0026#34;\n          }\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/uni-image-full-width\u003e\n\n\n  \n\n  \n    \u003cdiv data-component=\"uni-article-paragraph\" role=\"presentation\" data-analytics-module=\"{\n           \u0026#34;module_name\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Paragraph\u0026#34;,\n           \u0026#34;section_header\u0026#34;: \u0026#34;Take a look at our 2025 summer travel trends\u0026#34;\n         }\"\u003e\n        \u003cp data-block-key=\"5mt2k\"\u003eNow just be sure to leave a little extra room for a souvenir or two (or three)!\u003c/p\u003e\n      \u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\n            \n            \n\n            \n              \n\n\n\n\n            \n          \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/article\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
